# Database Assignment System Patterns

## Table Design Principles

### Assignment Tables Structure
The assignment system uses a dual-table approach for flexibility:

#### Main Assignment Tables
- **`lesson_assignments`** - Assigns lessons to courses/students
- **`assignment_assignments`** - Assigns homework to courses/students

Both tables follow the same pattern:
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS lesson_assignments (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  lesson_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES lessons(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  
  -- Assignment target (either course or individual students)
  course_id TEXT, -- Google Classroom course ID (optional)
  assigned_students UUID[], -- Array of student UUIDs (optional)
  
  -- Assignment details
  assigned_by TEXT NOT NULL,
  assigned_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  due_date TIMESTAMPTZ,
  
  -- Status and analytics
  total_assigned INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  total_started INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  total_completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  
  -- Constraints
  CHECK (course_id IS NOT NULL OR assigned_students IS NOT NULL),
  CHECK (NOT (course_id IS NOT NULL AND assigned_students IS NOT NULL))
);
```

#### Individual Progress Tables
- **`student_lesson_assignments`** - Individual student progress on lessons
- **`student_assignment_assignments`** - Individual student progress on homework

### Key Design Decisions

#### Flexible Assignment Targeting
Use CHECK constraints to ensure exactly one targeting method:
```sql
-- Must assign to course OR students, but not both
CHECK (course_id IS NOT NULL OR assigned_students IS NOT NULL),
CHECK (NOT (course_id IS NOT NULL AND assigned_students IS NOT NULL))
```

#### Array-Based Student Assignment
Store multiple student IDs efficiently:
```sql
assigned_students UUID[], -- Array of student UUIDs
```

Query individual assignments:
```sql
SELECT * FROM lesson_assignments 
WHERE assigned_students @> ARRAY['student-uuid']::UUID[];
```

#### Comprehensive Status Tracking
Use enums for consistent status values:
```sql
status TEXT DEFAULT 'assigned' CHECK (
  status IN ('assigned', 'started', 'in_progress', 'completed', 'overdue')
)
```

## Automatic Data Management

### Trigger Functions
Automatically create individual student assignments when assigning to courses:

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION create_student_lesson_assignments()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  -- If assigning to a course, create individual student assignments
  IF NEW.course_id IS NOT NULL THEN
    INSERT INTO student_lesson_assignments (lesson_assignment_id, student_id)
    SELECT NEW.id, s.id
    FROM students s
    WHERE s.course_id = NEW.course_id
      AND s.is_active = TRUE
      AND s.enrollment_state = 'ACTIVE';
    
    -- Update total_assigned count
    UPDATE lesson_assignments 
    SET total_assigned = (
      SELECT COUNT(*)
      FROM students 
      WHERE course_id = NEW.course_id 
        AND is_active = TRUE 
        AND enrollment_state = 'ACTIVE'
    )
    WHERE id = NEW.id;
  END IF;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;
```

### Analytics Updates
Automatically update completion statistics:
```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_lesson_assignment_analytics()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  UPDATE lesson_assignments 
  SET 
    total_started = (
      SELECT COUNT(*)
      FROM student_lesson_assignments 
      WHERE lesson_assignment_id = NEW.lesson_assignment_id
        AND status IN ('started', 'in_progress', 'completed')
    ),
    total_completed = (
      SELECT COUNT(*)
      FROM student_lesson_assignments 
      WHERE lesson_assignment_id = NEW.lesson_assignment_id
        AND status = 'completed'
    ),
    updated_at = NOW()
  WHERE id = NEW.lesson_assignment_id;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;
```

## Query Patterns

### Efficient Assignment Retrieval
Use proper joins for comprehensive data:
```sql
SELECT 
  la.*,
  l.title as lesson_title,
  l.description as lesson_description,
  c.name as course_name,
  c.student_count,
  COUNT(sla.id) as assigned_count,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN sla.status = 'completed' THEN 1 END) as completed_count
FROM lesson_assignments la
JOIN lessons l ON la.lesson_id = l.id
LEFT JOIN courses c ON la.course_id = c.google_course_id
LEFT JOIN student_lesson_assignments sla ON la.id = sla.lesson_assignment_id
WHERE la.is_active = true
  AND la.published = true
GROUP BY la.id, l.id, c.id
ORDER BY la.assigned_at DESC;
```

### Student Assignment Queries
Efficient student-specific queries:
```sql
-- Get all assignments for a student
SELECT 
  sla.*,
  la.due_date,
  la.instructions,
  l.title,
  l.description,
  l.estimated_time
FROM student_lesson_assignments sla
JOIN lesson_assignments la ON sla.lesson_assignment_id = la.id
JOIN lessons l ON la.lesson_id = l.id
WHERE sla.student_id = $1
  AND la.is_active = true
  AND la.published = true
ORDER BY la.assigned_at DESC;
```

### Overdue Assignment Detection
Use date functions for overdue queries:
```sql
-- Find overdue assignments
SELECT 
  sla.*,
  la.due_date,
  la.title,
  s.name as student_name,
  s.email as student_email
FROM student_lesson_assignments sla
JOIN lesson_assignments la ON sla.lesson_assignment_id = la.id
JOIN students s ON sla.student_id = s.id
WHERE la.due_date < NOW()
  AND sla.status NOT IN ('completed', 'graded')
  AND la.is_active = true
ORDER BY la.due_date ASC;
```

## Index Strategy

### Performance Indexes
Create indexes on frequently queried columns:
```sql
-- Assignment queries
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_lesson_id ON lesson_assignments(lesson_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_course_id ON lesson_assignments(course_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_assigned_by ON lesson_assignments(assigned_by);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_due_date ON lesson_assignments(due_date);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_published ON lesson_assignments(published);

-- Student assignment queries
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_student_lesson_assignments_student_id ON student_lesson_assignments(student_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_student_lesson_assignments_status ON student_lesson_assignments(status);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_student_lesson_assignments_lesson_assignment_id ON student_lesson_assignments(lesson_assignment_id);

-- Array search optimization
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_lesson_assignments_assigned_students ON lesson_assignments USING GIN (assigned_students);
```

### Composite Indexes
For complex queries:
```sql
-- Student + status queries
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_student_assignments_student_status 
ON student_lesson_assignments(student_id, status);

-- Assignment + date queries
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_assignments_active_due_date 
ON lesson_assignments(is_active, published, due_date);
```

## Data Integrity

### Foreign Key Constraints
Maintain referential integrity:
```sql
-- Lesson assignments must reference valid lessons
lesson_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES lessons(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,

-- Student assignments must reference valid assignments and students
lesson_assignment_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES lesson_assignments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
student_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES students(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
```

### Unique Constraints
Prevent duplicate assignments:
```sql
-- One assignment record per student per lesson assignment
UNIQUE(lesson_assignment_id, student_id)
```

### Check Constraints
Enforce business rules:
```sql
-- Progress percentage must be valid
progress_percentage INTEGER DEFAULT 0 CHECK (progress_percentage >= 0 AND progress_percentage <= 100),

-- Valid status values
status TEXT DEFAULT 'assigned' CHECK (status IN ('assigned', 'started', 'in_progress', 'completed', 'overdue')),

-- Assignment targeting rules
CHECK (course_id IS NOT NULL OR assigned_students IS NOT NULL),
CHECK (NOT (course_id IS NOT NULL AND assigned_students IS NOT NULL))
```

## Migration Patterns

### Safe Schema Updates
Always use IF NOT EXISTS for additive changes:
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS lesson_assignments (
  -- table definition
);

CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_name ON table_name(column);

ALTER TABLE table_name ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS new_column TEXT;
```

### Trigger Management
Drop and recreate triggers for updates:
```sql
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS trigger_name ON table_name;
CREATE TRIGGER trigger_name
  AFTER INSERT OR UPDATE ON table_name
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION function_name();
```

## API Integration Patterns

### Supabase Query Building
Use proper query construction:
```typescript
// TypeScript query building
let query = supabase
  .from('lesson_assignments')
  .select(`
    *,
    lesson:lessons(id, title, slug, description),
    course:courses!lesson_assignments_course_id_fkey(id, name, section),
    student_assignments:student_lesson_assignments(
      id, status, progress_percentage,
      student:students(id, name, email)
    )
  `)
  .eq('is_active', true)
  .eq('published', true)
  .order('assigned_at', { ascending: false })

// Apply filters conditionally
if (courseId) query = query.eq('course_id', courseId)
if (assignedBy) query = query.eq('assigned_by', assignedBy)
```

### Error Handling
Handle database errors gracefully:
```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('lesson_assignments')
  .insert(assignmentData)

if (error) {
  console.error('Database error:', error)
  
  // Handle specific error types
  if (error.code === '23505') { // Unique violation
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Assignment already exists' }, { status: 409 })
  }
  
  if (error.code === '23503') { // Foreign key violation
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Referenced record not found' }, { status: 400 })
  }
  
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Database error' }, { status: 500 })
}
```

## Backup and Maintenance

### Regular Maintenance
Clean up old assignment data:
```sql
-- Archive completed assignments older than 1 year
UPDATE lesson_assignments 
SET is_active = false 
WHERE created_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '1 year'
  AND total_completed = total_assigned;

-- Clean up reminder records for completed assignments
DELETE FROM assignment_reminders 
WHERE is_sent = true 
  AND created_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days';
```

### Performance Monitoring
Monitor slow queries and optimize:
```sql
-- Find slow assignment queries
SELECT query, mean_time, calls 
FROM pg_stat_statements 
WHERE query LIKE '%lesson_assignments%'
ORDER BY mean_time DESC;
```